Please make 

[Template]    Create Basic Telemetry Report

and the variable info the test body.
Done

As discussed, please create a separate test case and check if the telemetry report is being generated for different MetricDefinitions (which are supported by HMC, such as total_power and Ambient_0_Temp), and verify the telemetry report.

Done - added template to indicate separate testcases. I have decided to remove earlier testcase that tested only ambient temperature. This template formation includes that making that redundant.Thanks.
I dont see that you have created a separated test case for new ones. If you want to keep them as part of existing please make the changes as suggested.
Thanks for your review.
no need to create separate variable for it. Use them directly
Done

Why do we need to pass expected_result and report name here. By default expected result is set to success so dont pass it. And when it comes to report name, take random name for the report in the keyword.

```
# Metric definition name.
total_power
Battery_Voltage
Ambient_0_Temp
```
Done - giving a random name inside keyword will have consequent report creation to have same report name leading to failure. I do not want to delete report immediately creation for other tests.
I have remove providing report name string externally. Now it will create random string inside the keyword.
If we provide these values over here then only these value will get tested. So its better to do as suggested in the recent comment in Create Basic Telemetry Report keyword.
George .. Any thought on this.

We earlier decided to keep test data - like report type, collection type externally as template parameters. Lets stick to that. 
Giving any test data internally  inside the keyword is not a good test idea. Lets keep them visible.

When we are doing `Delete All Telemetry Reports` at test teardown then why it is required at suite teardown.

Also add the reason for adding Redfish power on in the suite teardown.
It is my choice to add extra precautionary measure.
We should not be adding unless its required. So please remove it.
It is better programmer technique for precaution; there is no harm and no extra overhead as such for delete attempt if reports are already deleted.

If we are deleting two times then we will not come to know when the delete fails one time. So its always good to add when only its required.

George... Any thoughts?

We do testing on telemetry report creation. Before and after the test, our job is to confirm cleaning all the existing reports. If we do multiple times cleaning, Before and after the test, it does not matter.
As discussed, we should be taking ramdon value from the supported list for MetricReportDefinitionType, ReportActions  and Metrics so that all these values get tested.
Done - Metrics properties like sensor path are not provided by externally by user, they are retrieved from provided metric definition  as already discussed.
Dont keep blank like after If line
Done

Keep capital letter for v in Verify in the comment. You can also reword like below.

```
# Verify that the created report has all the attributes provided at the time of creation
```
Done
Thanks

Add it like below in this keyword to use random value. If random values are also allowed for others like Metrics, ReportUpdates and AppendLimit than also use it.

```
${random_report_name}=  Generate Random String  8  [LETTERS]
${random_metric_definition_type}=  Set Random  ${supported_metric_definition_type}
${random_report_action}=  Set Random  ${supported_report_action}

    ${body}=  Catenate  {"Id": "${random_report_name}",
    ...  "MetricReportDefinitionType": "${random_metric_definition_type}",
    ...  "Name": "Report",
    ...  "ReportActions":["${random_report_action}"],
    ...  "Metrics":[{"CollectionDuration": "PT30.000S",
    ...  "MetricProperties":${resp["MetricProperties"]}}],
    ...  "ReportUpdates": "AppendWrapsWhenFull",
    ...  "AppendLimit":10,
    ...  "Schedule": {"RecurrenceInterval": "PT5.000S"}}
    
 ```
 
Add supported list in the variable like below
 
 *** Variables ***
@{supported_metric_definition_type}  Periodic  OnRequest
@{supported_report_action}           LogToMetricReportsCollection  etc

I had already added code for report name to be generated random way. 
However, report action, definition etc., will be provided from outside from the testcase where such test data will be visible. Keeping test data inside keyword is not a very good idea.I am keeping them.
The test data we are passing for this keyword is a random one except for metric definition. So it is better to use all in the keyword itself.

The testdata is not actually random, it is carefully selected so that available/common to all types of systems etc.

Additionally, I would not let keyword to select testdata randomly. I would give tester freedom to choose testdata with  clear intent.

Keeping testdata hidden within a library / keyword is not a very good practice either. So, keeping this for testdata to be visible,easily modifiable (add / delete / modify) in main test script for any future consideration.

instead of resp2 you can use redfish_output. Also compare the value with the random which was set.

        Should Be True  '${redfish_output.dict["MetricReportDefinitionType"]}' == '${random_metric_definition_type}'
        Should Be True  '${redfish_output.dict["ReportActions"][0]}' == '${random_report_action}'
        Should Be True  '${redfish_output.dict["Metrics"]}[0][MetricProperties][0]' == '${resp["MetricProperties"][0]}'
Done - modified resp2 keeping rest unchanged.
I have remove providing report name string externally. Now it will create random string inside the keyword.
Thanks !
All comments except those of keeping testdata inside keyword is incorporated. Thanks.
Thanks for reviewing !

always follow a consistent approach in naming here like below


    # Metric Definition  Metric Report Definition Type   Report Actions       Append Limit
